  documentation: "Subscribes to race banner data published by tinyskiesGlobeAtmospheric under `tinyskies/raceBanners` and to player state (qx/qy/qz/qw quaternion components, altitude, heading, vehicleType) published by tinyskiesFlightController. State machine: idle → approaching (banner near, fill 3-2-1 ring) → racing (timer + 12 checkpoints) → win/lose → idle. Banners hidden during race via `tinyskies/raceBannersVisibilityCommand`. Constants verbatim from source RaceManager.ts:26-50. Approximations: holo torus shader uses MeshStandardNodeMaterial with TSL emissive instead of source's raw GLSL holoVert/holoFrag (WebGPU compatibility). Bonus diamond mesh uses OctahedronGeometry instead of source's createPlaneCollectibleDiamondGeometry (visually equivalent collectible). Surface altitude approximated as globeRadius (no per-checkpoint terrain displacement query). Audio SFX cues published to `tinyskies/raceSfxCue` for any audio behavior to consume."
