  version: "1.0.0"
  description: "Glowing lantern clusters drifting on the globe surface; brighter at night."
  documentation: "5 clusters of 14 glowing lanterns each (~70 total), placed at deterministic seeded random positions on the globe surface (CLUSTER_ALTITUDE 0.55 above radius). Each lantern bobs + sways with sin/cos phase. PointsNodeMaterial with a procedural radial-gradient sprite texture (warm orange core, deep red edge — matches source FloatingLanterns.ts:43-66 fragment shader). Alpha = 0.3 + 0.7 × nightWeight (always faintly visible by day, brightest at night). Source uses InstancedMesh + BoxGeometry; the WebGPU port uses PointsNodeMaterial + sprite for cheaper per-frame mutation."
